<section class=" bg-white py-5">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center">
      <div class="col-lg-6 mt-5 mt-lg-0 mt-0">
        <p class="lead text-dark mb-3 ">Hi! I'm Josh. I really like open-source. It's not only good for the environment, but also a great learning tool.</p>
        <p class="mb-3">When I was starting my Ruby on Rails journey in 2011, I attributed a lot of my good code to that of others. This was made possible by open-source projects.</p>
        <p class="mb-3">I would visit <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20130512052803/http://www.opensourcerails.com/" target=_blank>OpenSourceRails.com</a> almost daily, looking for inspiration and how other people wrote code. It was invaluable to me. However, like all good things, it has moved on.</p>
        <p class="mb-3">After receiving the nod from <a href="https://github.com/jacquescrocker" target="_blank">Jacques Crocker</a>, the original creator of OpenSourceRails.com, I created my own directory of open-source Rails projects with a small twist: a short synopsis and tagging. Thanks Jacques!</p>
        <p class="mb-3">I'm an occasional writer of technical-ish stuff, and fraud, sometimes piracy, and sometimes pizza at <a href="https://www.josh.mn">www.josh.mn</a> and I can be found on most places on the internet as <abbr>joshmn</abbr>.</p>
        <% if false %>
        <%= turbo_frame_tag :newsletter_error %>
        <%= turbo_frame_tag :newsletter do %>
          <%= simple_form_for :newsletter, url: :newsletter, data: { 'turbo-frame': :newsletter } do |f| %>
            <div class="input-group mb-3">
              <%= f.input_field :email_address, placeholder: "Your email address", class: "form-control", style: "height: 50px;" %>
              <div class="input-group-append">
                <button class="btn btn-black" data-text="Sign up for the newsletter"><span>Sign up for my newsletter</span></button>
              </div>
            </div>
          <% end %>
          <p style="font-size:14px;">I send a brief, fun-to-read newsletter on the second Wednesday of each month with some bite-sized Railsisms and more from around the Rails community.</p>

        <% end %>
          <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
